- The Grateful Dead, St. Stephen piped.video/watch?v=g6mS-drQ… I have often written that opinions are like butts - everyone has one. Vitriolic, partisan discourse in politics has been a low note these days. And, too often we debate markets with the same source of dogma and lack of

objectivity that exists in our political debates. I can almost tell how someone will interpret the markets (Bull or Bear or something in between) by the person that voices their views. In general, views have become predictable despite the existence of so much uncertainty and

possible outcomes (many of them adverse). I find this predetermination odd. (It takes many market forms - from Perma Bull to Perma Bear, from gold bugs to those that recoil at the suggestion of purchasing precious metals. In politics it is Liberal v. Conservative, Democrat v.

Republican). And something to avoid. @jimcramer @tomkeene @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney @riskreversal @ferrotv @andrewrsorkin @beckyquick @carlquintanilla @terranovajoe @guyadami @SaraEisen @threadreaderapp unroll
